    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 10 August 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">They badly need the Emperor to stay unhurt after having
                            crossed over to Africa without any loss of life and having fought at
                            Tunis. He has settled the Milan affair so that they can relax. Why is
                            Oláh asking what will become of the Hungarian affairs? He should relax
                            and stay hopeful. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Di boni! Quantum fortunae et <persName>caesaris</persName> Dei
                    nostri integritati debemus, qui postquam in Aphricam traiecit, nullo ferme suo
                    milite desiderato et stagni fauces et Dunetum<note xml:id="note.1">Instead of
                        Tunetum, i.e. Tunis.</note> ipsum intra paucos dies expugnavit. Nos certe id
                    est, rem Mediolanensem ita firmavit, ut otiose nunc <quote xml:id="quote.1">in
                        utramque <pb/> aurem dormiamus.</quote><note type="quote"
                        xml:id="note.quote.1">Proverb., cf. Erasm. <hi rend="italic">Adag</hi>. 719.
                        I, VIII, 19. In utramvis dormire aurem. and Esop. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Fab</hi>. 47. De vulpe, cane et gallo.</note> Quid quaeris, et res
                    Hungarica in eadem navi, quam primum erit? Fac igitur, bono animo sis, et
                    meliora in horas sperabis. Maiestatem reginalem bene valere optamus, et te, quem
                    principes mei salutant, <persName>Scepero</persName><note xml:id="note.2"
                        >Cornelis de Schepper.</note> item ceteris amicis meis me commenda. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Mediolano</placeName> X. Augusti MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
